keyFacts: The document is a TECS Person Encounter List generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on September 20, 2021, showing travel history for Carrie Carrier.
Carrie Carrier had five recorded flight arrivals between July 1997 and January 2000 at airports in New York, Miami, Philadelphia, and Toronto.
All entries are marked as 'AIRLINE (NOT API)', indicating they were not processed through Advanced Passenger Information systems.
The document is marked 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive', suggesting it was part of an investigative file.
The travel pattern shows international travel between the U.S. and Canada during the late 1990s.
